The paper is about document ranking for web search, which is a classic problem in information retrieval (IR) and falls under the cs.IR sub-category. The proposed model uses deep neural networks to learn both local and distributed representations of text, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and falls under the cs.CL sub-category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG sub-category, which focuses on machine learning and deep learning. Additionally, the paper involves the use of learned representations, which is a common theme in the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.CV sub-category, which deals with computer vision and image processing, as the proposed model involves the use of distributed representations that are similar to those used in image recognition tasks.
